\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 We have already indicated in \\cref\{ontological-commitment\} the importance of the ontological commitment for the modelling language. Contemporary modelling frameworks yield meta-models that have a clear engineering focus which is very suitable for forward-looking, prescriptive (system) models. At the same time, these ontological commitments fall short for backward-looking, descriptive models. We consider domain ontologies, which naturally evolve on foundational ontologies (that express an ontological commitment), a necessary component to faithfully describe the domain of interpretation and formally represent the domain of interest. It is in the interest of the }
